  "articleSummary": "The article argues that modern developer laptops are no longer safe local environments but \"credential warehouses\" where one bad click can expose browser sessions, SSH keys, cloud CLI configs, and forgotten database exports. It sets the threat level at \"assume a process can run as you for a few minutes,\" citing infostealers like Lumma and the Snowflake breach as evidence that attackers target local credentials rather than exotic exploits. The tone is an urgent warning, framed through metaphors of unlocked desk drawers and production backups without alarms, aimed at developers and technical professionals who still treat local machines as low-risk.",
